1.40
Hover & click on the images for description

Description

Description:
Appends array2 to the back of array1 modifying array1. See insert for an "appendUnique" equivalent.
ⓘappend does not return array, it modifies the existing array. If you need to return a copy, use "+": Copyarray3 = array1 + array2;
Groups:
Arrays
Syntax

Syntax:
array1 append array2Parameters:
array1: Array
array2: ArrayReturn Value:
Nothing
Examples

Example 1:Copy_arr = [1,2,3];
_arr append [4,5,6];
hint str _arr; // [1,2,3,4,5,6]

Additional Information

See also:
set pushBack pushBackUnique insert + apply select resize reverse count deleteAt deleteRange

