Heeeere's Johnny! - c
Posted on Mar 09, 2015 - 00:41 (UTC)


Copy_array1 append _array2;
is roughly 1.2× faster (depending on array size) than
Copy_array1 = _array1 + _array2
(Averaged over 10.000 iterations with two identical arrays containing the numbers 0 through 9)

The larger the arrays to append, the faster append is as it does not create a new array, which happens with array addition.



Killzone_Kid - c
Posted on May 21, 2015 - 10:27 (UTC)


Array "unshift" implementation using append, a faster alternative to BIS_fnc_arrayUnShift:
CopyKK_fnc_unshift = {
private ["_arr", "_tmp"];
	_arr = _this select 0;
	_tmp = [_this select 1];
	_tmp append _arr;
	_arr resize 0;
	_arr append _tmp;
	_arr
};

// Example
arr = [1,2,3];
[arr, 0] call KK_fnc_unshift; // both arr and return of function are [0,1,2,3]



Killzone_Kid - c
Posted on May 21, 2015 - 15:21 (UTC)


Array "insert" implementation using append, much faster alternative to BIS_fnc_arrayInsert:
CopyKK_fnc_insert = {
private ["_arr", "_i", "_res"];
	_arr = _this select 0;
	_i = _this select 2;
	_res = [];
	_res append (_arr select [0, _i]);
	_res append (_this select 1);
	_res append (_arr select [_i, count _arr - _i]);
	_res;
};

// Example
arr = [1,2,3,4];
[arr, ["a","b"], 2] call KK_fnc_insert; // [1,2,"a","b",3,4]



Killzone_Kid - c
Posted on May 21, 2015 - 15:52 (UTC)


A faster alternative to BIS_fnc_arrayPushStack using append:
CopyKK_fnc_pushStack = {
_this select 0 append (_this select 1);
	_this select 0
};

// Example
arr = [1,2,3];
[arr, [4,5,6]] call KK_fnc_pushStack; // both arr and function return are [1,2,3,4,5,6]

1.92
Hover & click on the images for description

Description

Description:
Gets interpolated value based on Bézier curve with given control points (progress value is 0...1 for a curve that starts at pos0 and finishes at posN) 

Groups:
Math
Syntax

Syntax:
progress bezierInterpolation positionsParameters:
progress: Number - interpolation value
positions: Array of Arrays in format Position3DReturn Value:
Array - a single point position in format Position3D based on progress value
Examples

Example 1:Quick demonstration that spawns some spheres around player object:
Copyfor "_i" from 0 to 1 step 0.05 do {
createVehicle ["Sign_Sphere10cm_F", (_i bezierInterpolation [
player modelToWorld [0,0,0],
		player modelToWorld [0,2,2],
		player modelToWorld [2,0,2],
		player modelToWorld [0,0,4]
]), [], 0, "CAN_COLLIDE"];
};Example 2:Create a map marker curve from 4 control points with overlap (progress is -0.5...1.5 instead of 0...1):
Copyprivate _controlPoints = [[100,-90], [200,-30], [150,60], [100,90]] apply { player getRelPos _x };
{
private _marker = createMarkerLocal [str _x, _x];
	_marker setMarkerTypeLocal "mil_objective";
	_marker setMarkerTextLocal ("P" + str _forEachIndex);
}
forEach _controlPoints;

for "_i" from -0.5 to 1.5 step 0.01 do
{
private _marker = createMarkerLocal [str _i, _i bezierInterpolation _controlPoints];
	_marker setMarkerTypeLocal "mil_dot";
};
openMap true;

Additional Information

See also:
linearConversion vectorLinearConversion

